79.9	Scapegoat	Scapegoat	In modern usage a scapegoat may be a child, employee, peer, ethnic or religious group, or country singled out for unmerited negative treatment or blame. A whipping boy or "fall guy" is a form of scapegoat.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/William_Holman_Hunt_-_The_Scapegoat.jpg/240px-William_Holman_Hunt_-_The_Scapegoat.jpg
